DAUD OLATUNJI The Federal Government on Saturday empowered  3,500 rural and vulnerable  women in Ogun State with a grant of N20,000 each. The Minister of Humanitarian Affairs, Disaster Management and Social Development, Sadiya Farouq, presented the sum of N7m  to the beneficiaries at the commencement of  the Rural Woman Project in Abeokuta. Farouq  explained that the women were carefully selected from different rural areas in the state. Farouq, who was represented by the Permanent Secretary of the ministry, Bashir  Alkali, said the initiative was part of the programmes lined  up for the National Social Investment Programme as a strategy for reducing poverty and enhancing social inclusion. In her remarks, the Deputy Governor, Mrs Noimot  Salako-Oyedele, commended the Federal Government for its efforts towards lifting many vulnerable citizens out of poverty. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com   